      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A calm and professional UI for a banking app sounds like a great project. You can't go wrong with a deep navy blue like #000080 as the primary color - it's a classic choice that exudes trust and stability. As for complementary colors, I'd recommend a crisp white (#FFFFFF) to create a sense of contrast and highlight important elements. A soft silver or gray (#C7C5B8) can also work well to add a touch of sophistication and balance out the bold navy blue.\n\nFor analogous colors, you could consider a palette that features different shades of blue, such as #032B44 (a darker, richer blue) and #4682B4 (a lighter, more muted blue). These colors will create a cohesive look and feel, while also providing a nice range of shades to work with. You could also experiment with adding a hint of gold or copper (#FFD700 or #FFC400) to give your UI a touch of luxury and high-end feel.\n\nIn terms of textures and patterns, consider using subtle geometric patterns or organic shapes to add visual interest without overwhelming the user. A simple, high-quality font like Open Sans or Montserrat will also help to create a clean and professional look.",
